Package ohos.event.notification

Class NotificationUserInput

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.event.notification.NotificationUserInput
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class NotificationUserInput
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Defines the user input, which will be passed together with an intent in a sent IntentAgent. You should always use NotificationUserInput.Builder to create instances of this class. You can call NotificationActionButton.Builder#addNotificationUserInput(NotificationUserInput) to add a NotificationUserInput object to a NotificationActionButton.
    Since:
    3
    SystemCapability
    SystemCapability.Notification#ANS

      • addMimeInputToIntent

        public static void addMimeInputToIntent​(NotificationUserInput userInput,
                                        Intent intent,
                                        Map<String,Uri> results)
        Adds the given NotificationUserInput object of a specified MIME type to an Intent. This method is similar to addInputsToIntent(java.util.List<ohos.event.notification.NotificationUserInput>, ohos.aafwk.content.Intent, ohos.utils.PacMap) except that the MIME type must be specified.
        Parameters:
        userInput - Indicates the NotificationUserInput object for which the input results are provided.
        intent - Indicates the Intent to which the input results are to be added.
        results - Indicates a map containing the MIME type and its URI result.
        Since:
        3

      • addInputsToIntent

        public static void addInputsToIntent​(List<NotificationUserInput> userInputs,
                                     Intent intent,
                                     PacMap pacMap)
        Adds a list of NotificationUserInput objects to an Intent. This method should only be called by user input collection services when sending input results to an IntentAgent.
        Parameters:
        userInputs - Indicates the list of NotificationUserInput objects for which the input results are provided.
        intent - Indicates the Intent to which the input results are to be added.
        pacMap - Indicates the PacMap object holding the input results. The PacMap key must match the keys contained in the objects specified in userInputs.
        Since:
        3

      • getMimeInputsFromIntent

        public static Map<String,Uri> getMimeInputsFromIntent​(Intent intent,
                                                      String inputKey)
        Obtains the input results of a particular MIME type from a specified ohos.aafwk.content.Intent. This method is similar to getInputsFromIntent(ohos.aafwk.content.Intent) but uses the key of the NotificationUserInput.
        Parameters:
        intent - Indicates the Intent containing the user input results.
        inputKey - Indicates the key of the NotificationUserInput results to obtain.
        Returns:
        Returns a map containing the MIME type and its URI result.
        Since:
        3

      • toString

        public String toString​()
        Description copied from class: Object
        Returns a string representation of the object. In general, the toString method returns a string that "textually represents" this object. The result should be a concise but informative representation that is easy for a person to read. It is recommended that all subclasses override this method.

        The toString method for class Object returns a string consisting of the name of the class of which the object is an instance, the at-sign character `@', and the unsigned hexadecimal representation of the hash code of the object. In other words, this method returns a string equal to the value of: 

         getClass().getName() + '@' + Integer.toHexString(hashCode())
